Class MemoryMapper<A,B,C,D>

  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    MapSequence.Map

    public class MemoryMapper<A,B,C,D>
extends org.apache.hadoop.mapreduce.Mapper<A,B,C,D>
    MemoryMapper supports in-memory mapping for a chain of consecutive mappers. This provides significant performance improvements as each map need not write its results to disk. Note that MemoryMapper is not general-purpose and is specific to Faunus' current MapReduce library. In particular, it assumes that the chain of mappers emits 0 or 1 key/value pairs for each input.
    Author:
    Marko A. Rodriguez (http://markorodriguez.com)
